The paper proposes a novel approach for preventing discrimination in automated decision processes, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and the focus on learning a distribution and translating between different distributions suggest that the paper is most likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of GANs for data sanitization and the focus on fairness and interpretability suggest that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the use of a local sanitizer that can be applied to new data suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
